Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
routePGPinUseSignalRoute(25.10)                routePGPinUseSignalRoute(25.10)

Name
       routePGPinUseSignalRoute  -  Routes  the secondary power/ground pins of
       always-on cells to the specified power/ground nets in signal route

Syntax
       routePGPinUseSignalRoute

       [help]

       [-all]

       [-maxFanout number]

       [-nets {listofNets}]

       [-nonDefaultRule ruleName]

       [-pattern {trunk | steiner}]

       [-well]

       Routes the secondary power/ground pins of always-on cells to the speci-
       fied power/ground nets in signal route. You can also control the  rout-
       ing  pattern  and wire by specifying the pattern, the maximum number of
       pins per cluster, and non-default rules.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each routePGPinUseSignalRoute parameter.

              For  a  detailed  description of the command and all its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man routePGPinUseSignalRoute

       -all   Routes non-primary power/ground pins of all the cells.

       -nets <listOfNets>
              Specifies the power/ground nets to be connected to the secondary
              power/ground pins.

              Default: If this parameter is not specified, the  software  will
              get  all the nets from global connections for the cells and pins
              defined in the command setPGPinUseSignalRoute.

       -pattern {trunk | steiner}
              Specifies  how  the   signal   router   routes   the   secondary
              power/ground pins.

              Trunk:  When  option  maxFanout  value  is 1, routes the pins to
              nearest power grid. When the value is more than  1,  routes  all
              pins per cluster to the trunk.

              Steiner: Routes all pins to a trunk.

              Default: trunk

       -maxFanout <number>
              Specifies  the  maximum  number of pins per cluster in the trunk
              rotating pattern.

              Default: 5.

       -nonDefaultRule <ruleName>
              Specifies the non-default rule the signal router uses  to  route
              the secondary power/ground pins.

              Default: Regular signal routing rule is used by default.

       -well  Includes nwell and pwell pins

              Type: Boolean, Optional

Related Information
              * getPGPinUseSignalRoute

              * setPGPinUseSignalRoute

              * Low Power Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide

